THIRD-PARTY LICENSES

This project depends on the following third-party components; each retains its original license.

- FastAPI — web framework (REST API) — MIT License
- Starlette — ASGI toolkit (used by FastAPI) — BSD 3-Clause License
- Uvicorn — ASGI server — BSD 3-Clause License
- firebase-admin — Google Cloud / Firestore access — Apache License 2.0
- openai (Python SDK) — calls OpenAI Assistant API — MIT License
- httpx — async HTTP client — BSD 3-Clause License
- gradio-client — optional client for external Gradio Space — Apache License 2.0
- Pydantic / pydantic-settings — data validation & config — MIT License
- SQLModel — data-model layer (future RDBMS support) — MIT License

A complete list of pinned versions appears in “requirements.txt”; all listed packages remain under their respective upstream licenses.

DATA USAGE AND PRIVACY

- AGaRiCleaner processes user-supplied text to provide toxicity evaluation and transformation.
• No personal data is permanently stored on the server.
• Text may be relayed to third-party APIs (OpenAI, optional Gradio Space, Google Firestore) only to fulfill user requests.
• API consumers are responsible for complying with local data-protection regulations (GDPR, etc.).
• Any external datasets you integrate must be used according to their original licenses and terms.

